%N A395849 Decimal expansion of the expected distance between the center of a unit-side regular pentagon to a randomly and uniformly selected point in its interior.
%H A395849 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395849 Equals (sqrt(10*(5 + sqrt(5))) + (5 + 2*sqrt(5))*arcsinh(sqrt(5 - 2*sqrt(5))))/30.
%F A395849 Equals (sqrt(5)*phi^2/30) * (2*tan(Pi/5) + phi*arcsinh(tan(Pi/5))), where phi is the golden ratio (A001622).
%e A395849 0.496444569290796108738306356392121041316243838956926...
%t A395849 RealDigits[(Sqrt[10*(5 + Sqrt[5])] + (5 + 2*Sqrt[5])*ArcSinh[Sqrt[5 - 2*Sqrt[5]]])/30, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395849 (PARI) (sqrt(10*(5 + sqrt(5))) + (5 + 2*sqrt(5))*asinh(sqrt(5 - 2*sqrt(5))))/30
%Y A395849 Cf. A001622, A019934, A245698 (equilateral triangle), A103712 (square), A245700 (regular hegagon), A010722 (disk), A152627 (ball), A135691 (cube), A395847.
